TopicTitle: Waiter, theres a _____________ in my soup!

Articles.Content:
Hmmm... *touches the soup to feel if it is oily, making the soup unsafe to eat because someone else touched it* Yep! Not oily at all. Enjoy, sir!

Waiter, there is an obscure reference in my soup!

Edited August 9, 2023 by TwoCalories
I felt a great disturbance in the Force, as if millions of voices suddenly cried out "New page," and were suddenly silenced.

It is ok, it has been folded into a boat shape and is floating on top.

I asked for some Swedish soup but based on the shark dorsal moving around in it, it must be Finnish.

Shark fin soup is illegal, sir. Homeland Security will be arriving shortly.

Waiter! There are no croutons in my bisque!

It is only a small Bisque, you might call it a Biscuit.

Some inspiration soup please.

No problem, sir, but we must inform police.

Waiter! Jinn with tonic, please.

Here is a lamp to rub, it has a Djinn with tonic inside it.

Waiter, can I separate the Hydrogen from my soup?

Here is some oxygen gas and a lighter. Do as you please.

Waiter, can you add some Rocket Propellant into the soup?

Here are some bagels and Lox.

Waiter, I see an eternity reflected in my soup.

The speed posting goes on for an eternity. Deal with it.

Waiter, why are you so mean?

Because it means.

Waiter! These beans are beaningless.

Use your imagination! Give them beaning!

Waiter! There is stew in my soup in my bisque in my broth in my noodles in my dip in my water!

Waiter: Maybe try closing your mouth when you chew, also thank you for ordering one of everything.

Customer: Waiter, I can remember when there was just a fly in my soup.

It's a French restaurant. You can enjoy the cup of fly broth, and the fly itself is cooked on another plate.

Waiter! Coffee and croissant with boiled sausage and ketchup.

Here, you go, all in one bowl. We call it a kerbiloid special.

Waiter, there is a speed run in my soup.

No, that's Dream doing a manhunt.

Waiter, there is a thing in my soup.

Waiter: Is it "The Thing"? Because we have been looking for "The Thing".

Waiter, there is a Siver Surfer in my soup.

I thought you wanted silver soup?

Waiter! There is graham's number pasta in my soup and it is making my soup into a black hole!

Don't be intimidated, black hole soup is actually quite delicious. Make sure to eat it down to the singularity; it's the best part!

Waiter, there's a hair in my black hole soup!

Black holes are hairless. It's from our cook's bald head.

Waiter! Carry curry!

Here is 2000 Tons of the hottest curry. *huffs and puffs*

It's an entangled noodle soup.

Waiter! Why is there a babygator in this egg?

Because it wanted to be like sheldon.
